      • compute

        @Contract(mutates="this")
public Value compute(@NotNull
                                                @NotNull java.lang.String address,
                                                @NotNull
                                                @NotNull java.util.function.UnaryOperator<Value> operator)
        Replace the value at the given address with the result of invoking the given operator with the current value.
        If the given operator thrown any exception when invoked by this method. The thrown exception will fall throw this method with nothing changed.
        The computing will be performed on the last frame that contain an allocation to the given address. If no frame has an allocation to the given address then the result of the computation will be store in the base frame.
        Parameters:
        address - the address to replace the value at.
        operator - the function to be invoked to acquire the replacement value.
        Returns:
        the computed value.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the given address or operator is null.
        Since:
        0.2.0 ~2021.05.21

      • popFrame

        @Contract(mutates="this")
public Frame popFrame()
        Pop the current stack frame. Popping the stack frame will result to this memory representing the frame previous to the last pushed frame. If the base frame to be popped, then the base frame will be replaced with a new one instead of popped.
        Returns:
        the popped frame.
        Since:
        0.2.0 ~2021.05.21
